 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lord of Swynfen Philip de Aust was born in 1248, in Swinfen, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons. He died in 1336, in Wall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 88."},"et":{"1248–1336":"1248–1336","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–1338":"–1338","1338":"1338","1248":"1248","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1275":"1275","Swinfen, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Swinfen, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1248–1336":"1248–1336","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–1338":"–1338","1338":"1338","1248":"1248","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1275":"1275","Swinfen, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Swinfen, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wall, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1248–1336":"1248–1336","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–1338":"–1338","1338":"1338","1248":"1248","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1275":"1275","Swinfen, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Swinfen, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Wall, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wall, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lord of Swynfen Philip de Aust est né en 1248, à Swinfen, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé en 1336, à Wall, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 88 ans."},"de":{"1248–1336":"1248–1336","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–1338":"–1338",